-- Monsoon Rainfall Deficit Narrows to 14%, India's Weather Department Says
-- Thomas Kutty Abraham
-- 2010-07-05T02:45:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/monsoon-rainfall-deficit-narrows-to-14-india-s-weather-department-says.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, narrowed to 14
percent as of yesterday, the weather office said.  
 The nation received 171.7 millimeters of rain in the June
1-July 4 period, compared with the 50-year average of 198.7
millimeters, the India Meteorological Department said on its
website. The monsoon was 16 percent below normal in June.  
